An exact and true relation of a most cruell and horrid murther committed by one of the cavaliers, on a woman in Leicester, billetted in her house: who was shot into the back, being within five weeks of the time of her delivery. Read in the house of Commons, and ordered to be forthwith printed and published: H: Elsynge, Cler. Parl. D. Com. England and Wales. Parliament.
7, [1] p.
Printed for E. Husbands and I. Franck, and are to be sold at their shops, in the middle Temple, and next door to the Kings-head in Fleetstreet, London : Sept. 17. 1642.
Signed at end by attending coroners: Francis Coltman, Thomas Todd. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
